    }
  ],
  "text": "The Grafana dashboard migration v38 bug is located in the table panel fieldConfig migration logic. The root cause is in apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go in the processPanelsV38 function (lines 90-133).\n\nThe flawed conditional logic is at lines 116-117:\n```go\nif defaults, ok := fieldConfig[\"defaults\"].(map[string]interface{}); ok {\n    if custom, ok := defaults[\"custom\"].(map[string]interface{}); ok {\n        // process custom\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFollowed by the critical migrateOverrides call at line 131:\n```go\nmigrateOverrides(fieldConfig)\n```\n\nThe bug occurs when panels have no explicit fieldConfig.defaults.custom but do have field overrides with custom.displayMode properties. The original buggy code likely had the migrateOverrides function call nested inside the conditional blocks (checking if defaults and/or custom exist), rather than at the outer scope. This caused overrides to be skipped when defaults.custom was missing, silently dropping table panel field override configuration.\n\nThe comment on line 130 explicitly states: \"This must be called regardless of whether defaults.custom exists\", which indicates the fix involved moving the migrateOverrides call outside the if blocks to ensure it executes for all panels, regardless of whether fieldConfig.defaults.custom exists.\n\nThe migrateOverrides function (lines 136-176) handles converting custom.displayMode properties in field overrides to the new custom.cellOptions format. Without this call, dashboards lacking explicit fieldConfig.defaults.custom would lose column width and text alignment settings stored in their field overrides.\n\nThe v38 schema migration is registered in migrations.go at line 74 as part of the standard migration chain."
}
